panels.description:
Branch age over time for each repository and branch (timeseries)

Query: vcs_ref_time{vcs_repository_name=~"$repo", team_name=~"$team"}

This time series shows the age of each branch in seconds over time. Each line represents a specific branch in a repository. The vcs_ref_time metric tracks how long branches have existed since creation from the default branch. Lines trending upward indicate aging branches that may need to be merged or cleaned up.

Total number of repositories for the team (stat)

Query: vcs_repository_count{team_name=~"$team"}

This stat shows the total count of repositories being monitored for the selected team. The vcs_repository_count metric provides a simple count of all repositories in the Azure DevOps project.

Age of each branch over time (timeseries)

Query: vcs_ref_time{vcs_repository_name=~"$repo", team_name=~"$team"}

This time series shows the age (in seconds) of each branch over time. Each line represents a specific branch. The vcs_ref_time metric measures how long each branch has existed since creation from the default branch. Consistently rising lines indicate aging branches. Short-lived branches that disappear quickly indicate healthy practices.

Count of open pull requests over time

Query: vcs_change_count{vcs_change_state="open", vcs_repository_name=~"$repo"}

This time series displays the number of open pull requests for each repository over time. The vcs_change_count metric is filtered for the open state. Each line represents a repository. Increasing trends may indicate review bottlenecks or accumulating PRs. Stable or decreasing trends suggest healthy PR throughput.

Age of each open pull request

Query: vcs_change_duration{vcs_repository_name=~"$repo", team_name=~"$team", vcs_change_state="open"}

This time series shows the age (in seconds) of each individual open pull request. Each line represents a specific PR. The vcs_change_duration metric tracks how long each PR has been in the open state. PRs aging as horizontal lines need attention. This helps identify stale PRs that may need follow-up or closure.

Count of merged pull requests over time

Query: vcs_change_count{vcs_change_state="merged", vcs_repository_name=~"$repo", team_name=~"$team"}

This time series shows the number of merged pull requests for each repository over time. The vcs_change_count metric is filtered for the merged state. Each line represents a repository. This tracks PR throughput and merge velocity. Higher values indicate more frequent merges, which is positive for continuous integration.

Time to merge for merged pull requests

Query: vcs_change_time_to_merge{vcs_repository_name=~"$repo", team_name=~"$team"}

This time series shows the time-to-merge (in seconds) for each merged pull request. The vcs_change_time_to_merge metric captures the duration from PR creation to merge. Each point represents a merged PR. Lower values indicate faster review and merge cycles, which is a key metric for small batch delivery and continuous integration.

Code coverage percentage by repository and branch (timeseries)

Query: vcs_code_coverage{vcs_repository_name=~"$repo", team_name=~"$team"}

This time series shows the code coverage percentage for each repository and branch over time. The vcs_code_coverage metric is collected from Azure DevOps build code coverage reports. Higher percentages indicate better test coverage. Dropping coverage may indicate new code without corresponding tests.
